<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="67.[128,654,1062,1501]" pageId="67" pageNumber="67">
COMMENTS: No type was designated in the original description, nor was there mention of the number of specimens available to Brehm. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert, E." box="[128,351,1301,1323]" pageId="67" pageNumber="67" pagination="4 - 63" refId="ref135665" refString="Hartert, E. 1918 a. Types of birds in the Tring Museum. A. Types in the Brehm Collection. Novitates Zoologicae 25: 4 - 63." type="journal article" year="1918">Hartert (1918a: 27)</bibRefCitation>
listed the above specimen as the type of 
<taxonomicName box="[306,376,1330,1353]" class="Aves" family="Paridae" genus="Parus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="67" pageNumber="67" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lugens">
<emphasis box="[306,376,1330,1353]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="67">lugens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, thereby designating it the 
<typeStatus box="[169,278,1361,1383]" pageId="67" pageNumber="67">lectotype</typeStatus>
. It is the only Brehm specimen of this form from 
<collectingCountry box="[308,389,1390,1411]" name="Greece" pageId="67" pageNumber="67">Greece</collectingCountry>
that came to AMNH. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kleinschmidt, O." box="[128,456,1420,1442]" pageId="67" pageNumber="67" pagination="45 - 103" refId="ref137524" refString="Kleinschmidt, O. 1897. Die palaearktischen Sumpfmeisen. Ornithologisches Jahrbuch 8: 45 - 103." type="journal article" year="1897">Kleinschmidt (1897: 95–96)</bibRefCitation>
gave this specimen the number ‘‘42’’ and illustrated its bill, but did not discuss it further.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
